Pre-Game Insights: Pakistan and England will clash against each other in the final of the T20 World Cup 2022 at MCG to lift their second T20 World Cup trophy.
With both teams on a winning run, the final between Pakistan and England is expected to be a close contest and go down the wire.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Pakistan and England are on a winning run and the final is expected to be a close contest.
The final of the T20 World Cup 2022 between Pakistan and England will be broadcasted on the Star Sports network on TV, and on OTT Platform Hotstar for Indian viewers.
Others: The probable playing XI for Pakistan includes Mohammad Rizwan, Babar Azam, Mohammad Haris, Shan Masood, Iftikhar Ahmed, Shadab Khan, Mohammad Nawaz, Mohammad Wasim Jr, Naseem Shah, Haris Rauf, Shaheen Afridi.
The probable playing XI for England includes Jos Buttler, Alex Hales, Philip Salt, Ben Stokes, Harry Brook, Liam Livingstone, Moeen Ali, Sam Curran, Chris Woakes, Chris Jordan/Mark Wood, Adil Rashid.
